{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-template-js","path":"/linux/unofficial-treble-support-for-nvidia-shield","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h2 id=\"check-support\" style=\"position:relative;\">Check support<a href=\"#check-support\" aria-label=\"check support permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<p>Check Treble support with <a href=\"https://gitlab.com/TrebleInfo/TrebleInfo/-/releases\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">TrebleInfo</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"treblize\" style=\"position:relative;\">Treblize<a href=\"#treblize\" aria-label=\"treblize permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<p>Of course Nvidia Shield Tablet doesn't support Treble. But this should be simple, it's just repartitioning and moving some folders around as I understood from <a href=\"https://forum.xda-developers.com/t/guide-q-a-treble-from-stock-to-treble-everything-you-need-to-know.3793734/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">this thread</a>.</p>\n<p>So let's get started.</p>\n<p>Do I need TWRP with Treble Manager (like <a href=\"https://forum.xda-developers.com/t/recovery-treble-twrp-3-3-1-0-with-tissot-manager.3976117/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">this</a>, or this <a href=\"https://forum.xda-developers.com/t/recovery-treble-retired-twrp-with-tissot-manager-treble-dual-boot-support.3793637/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">old version with screenshots</a>)?</p>\n<p>Behind the hood it's just this <a href=\"https://github.com/Giovix92/twrp_device_xiaomi_tissot/blob/android-9.0/recovery/root/tissot_manager/installer.sh#L73\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">list of instructions</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://forum.xda-developers.com/t/dev-how-to-compile-twrp-touch-recovery.1943625/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Here's</a> an explanation how to make TWRP for A/B devices</p>\n<p>This is my plan:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>From Lineage 15 read <code class=\"language-text\">/proc/cmdline</code>, check that <strong>selinux</strong> and <strong>dm-verity</strong> are disabled (we are going to change partitions and next boot should not fail just because partitions are changed)</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://forum.xda-developers.com/t/dev-how-to-compile-twrp-touch-recovery.1943625/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Build TWRP</a> with <strong>Treble Manager</strong> merged from <a href=\"https://github.com/Giovix92/twrp_device_xiaomi_tissot\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">this repo</a></li>\n<li></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Just in case <a href=\"https://forum.xda-developers.com/t/tool-tissot-low-level-backup-restore-unbrick-toolkit-for-mi-a1.3790307/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://forum.xda-developers.com/t/tool-tissot-low-level-backup-restore-unbrick-toolkit-for-mi-a1.3790307/</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"reference\" style=\"position:relative;\">Reference<a href=\"#reference\" aria-label=\"reference permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>A very broad steps on how to convert to Android 9 ROM to GSI compatible one <a href=\"https://4pda.to/forum/index.php?showtopic=892755&#x26;st=3380#entry75861460\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">link</a></li>\n<li>GitHub of legendary <a href=\"https://github.com/phhusson/treble_experimentations\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">phhusson</a></li>\n</ul>","excerpt":"Check support Check Treble support with TrebleInfo Treblize Of course Nvidia Shield Tablet doesn't support Treble. But this should be simple…","tableOfContents":"<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#check-support\">Check support</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#treblize\">Treblize</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#reference\">Reference</a></li>\n</ul>","fields":{"socialcard":"gatsby-plugin-social-card/b9de171a-5788-56a9-be71-618453e32b34.jpg"},"frontmatter":{"date":"July 07, 2023","published":"July 07, 2023","lastModified":"July 07, 2023","title":"Treble for NVIDIA Shield K1","subtitle":"Unofficial support","section":null,"draft":null,"developing":null,"butt